### Upstream OpenAI-compatible API quick tests
### Requires VS Code REST Client extension
### Talks directly to the upstream OpenAI-compatible endpoints.
### Adjust @host to point at your upstream (NOT the proxy).

@host = http://host.docker.internal:8000
@apiKey = change-me
@model = Qwen3.6

### Health check
GET {{host}}/v1/models HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

###

### List available models
GET {{host}}/v1/models HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

###

### Chat completions (non-streaming)
POST {{host}}/v1/chat/completions HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "Say hello in one sentence."}
  ],
  "stream": false
}

###

### Chat completions (streaming)
POST {{host}}/v1/chat/completions HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "Write a 1-line haiku about GPUs."}
  ],
  "stream": true
}

###

### Completions endpoint
POST {{host}}/v1/completions HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "prompt": "Complete this sentence in a friendly tone: Today is",
  "max_tokens": 32,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

###

### Embeddings endpoint
POST {{host}}/v1/embeddings HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "model": "{{model}}",
  "input": "Hello from direct upstream test"
}
